Date: Fri, 8 Nov 2019 14:30:34 -0500
Subject: drm/amd/display: have two different sr and pstate latency tables for
 renoir
Git-commit: 10bce710fa6feb13ec270d5420aad3b81f6bf7ea
Patch-mainline: v5.5-rc2
References: bsc#1152472

[Why]
new sr and pstate latencies are optimized for the case when we are not
using lpddr4 memory

[How]
have two different wm tables, one for the lpddr case and one for
non lpddr case

